    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The function "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "udf_ValidUserAccessDoer",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. Scalar functions return a single value and are used to encapsulate logic that can be reused across multiple queries or stored procedures. This function is designed to determine whether a user has valid access rights to perform certain actions within a system, based on the input parameters provided."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
